d and even the higher level people on RZ with the exception of a few wizards try to defend it, being able to kill someone and loot their fungi != balanced, and in the history of manaburn on RZ, only once has a person survived a manaburn, and that's Stynkfyst, the best geared monk on server, with full buffs, with 150+ AA points and against Xbena, a wizard with very very poor no drop, but manaburn and nexus gate, who has to date ganked 5+ fungi tunics and countless cloak of flames without any risk.. Balanced you say?  PFFT<br>
<br>
Manaburn out of the picture, about melee versus spells.  The problem is that melee is 'unresistable' for casters, while spells with the exceptions of lures are easily resistable.  While melee saves versus AC, spells save versus resists, with average gear for a level 60, full buffs I can break 800 ac, and that's with shissar/coe, and even that's absolutely useless versus a high level melee.  What I think needs to exist to balance out melee/caster pvp at the high end (which is totally skewed towards melee) is that caster AC needs to actually make a very significant impact on melee damage.  It is currently impossible for any caster to raise his AC to a point where it even makes a difference in pvp, while any joe schmoe, with 10 k investment can buy a full set of BD/Diamond gear and laugh at all regular spells.  I think it would add an element of tactic if before going into a battle, a wizard would have to choose whether to wear hp gear to combact lures, resist gear, or ac gear.<br>
<br>
At level 60, a rogue will land most hits for maximum against a wizard, simply because a wizards ac is A LOT lower than the mobs a level 60 rogue fights as a baseline, so his damage distribution is extremly skewed up, making it so that moving from 600 to 800 AC would hamper a melee's damage output as much as going from 25 to 120 to all resists is IMHO exactly what's needed for pvp, not stupid insta kill skills. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uauroreakengro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurore Akengro</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/02 8:28:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=95>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: At least I can read a question statement correctly....</span><hr size=1> Food plz Mearis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvelaelsoulrender.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Velael Soulrender</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/24/02 4:14:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=96>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mmogamers.com/hate/ikonboard/avatars/joe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: At least I can read a question statement correctly....</span><hr size=1> Fyvish (60 Primal Rogue) killed Cappadonna (60 epic wizard) within the casting time of Manaburn. /disc Duelist ... fully hasted that's 2 double BS rounds + God knows how much melee damage.<br>
